# Deploy

When the user says **deploy**, **ship**, or **publish** (to prod):

1. Run `git status` only.
2. If the working tree has notable undocumented user-facing changes, update docs/changelog first (see `maintain-project-docs` skill), then continue.
3. Otherwise run only:

```bash
export PATH="$HOME/.nvm/versions/node/v24.18.0/bin:$PATH"
cd rtikhonov.com && npm run deploy
```

Use network permissions. Expect ~30–60s. `npm run deploy` already runs `check:docs` and the build.

4. Reply with live URLs and the Wrangler Version ID. Live: `https://rtikhonov.com`, `https://www.rtikhonov.com`, `https://rtikhonov.inrome.workers.dev`.

## Do not

- TodoWrite for deploy
- `git diff main...HEAD` (or large branch diffs) unless the deploy failed
- Manual README / `docs/` / CHANGELOG review when `git status` is clean
- Separate `check:docs` or `astro build` before `npm run deploy`
- Commit or push unless the user asks

Agent shells often lack Node on PATH. Always export the nvm path above (or `source ~/.nvm/nvm.sh && nvm use`) before npm/astro/wrangler.
